h1 Home lighting and appliances

p This sector considers energy used for lighting and appliances (e.g. fridges, computers, televisions) in households.

p Note that at all levels, energy demand for cooking is fixed and assumed to grow with the number of households. Electrification of cooking is controlled by a separate lever. Excluding cooking, the electricity demand in 2012 is estimated at roughly 4,100 kWh per household.

h2 Level 1

p Level 1 assumes electricity demand per household stays constant at the 2012 level. 

h2 Level 2

p Level 2 assumes that electricity demand per household reduces to 33% below the 2012 level by 2050.

h2 Level 3

p Level 3 assumes that electricity demand per household reduces to 50% below the 2012 level by 2050.

h2 Level 4

p Level 3 assumes that electricity demand per household reduces to 67% below the 2012 level by 2050.

